tip.text: Beautiful palace, take the audio guide for an additional €3. Also you can take the opera station train which is a few meters away. Don't miss the gala dining room.

venue.name: Royal Palace of Madrid (Palacio Real de Madrid)

tip.text: One of the best hotel from the luxury collection. Sit outside in the courtyard and sip on a few cocktails. Cathedral and Royal Alcazars is minutes away. Immaculate service and a pristine property.

contact.facebookName: Hotel Alfonso XIII, Sevilla - The Luxury Collection

tip.text: Beautiful architecture and gardens! Do not miss the carvings on pine wood and stone. Visit Patio de las doncellas. Entry is €11 per person.

venue.name: Royal Alcazars of Seville (Real Alcázar de Sevilla)

tip.text: Beautiful ocean views! Eclipse their rooftop is a must visit. The staff is very courteous. They have private beach and an excellent spa!

formattedAddress: Plaça de la Rosa dels Vents, 1
location.address: Plaça de la Rosa dels Vents, 1

tip.text: Beautiful ocean view with great music, drinks and monstrous burger! Enjoy the breeze and sip on those cocktails!
Try the shrimp, spicy feta and lamb chops. The house wine is great too. Long waits, 6 credit card maximum. They have eggplant and tomato dish for vegetarians!
Excellent for dates and business meetings. Order the dim sum platter, spicy prawns, for vegetarians try the mock meat with black pepper sauce. Hakka noodles are amazing!
They have a beautiful rooftop and an excellent cocktail bar. The rooms are pretty modern. Located in the near the London eye.
This place has one of the best pizza and pasta hands down! Get the mushroom ravioli and margarita pizza! It's BYOB with a liquor store across the corner. Be ready to wait a bit.
Get the carnitas, try the shishito peppers. They have a grilled vegetables in green mole sauce which is a vegetarian. A great selection of cocktails.
A very trendy hotel with excellent breakfast buffet and service. The rooms are modern. The pool is beautiful and do relax and get a drink at the woobar!

formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10500
location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร

tip.text: Stay in a pool villa, be warned of the mosquito and outdated rooms. The shower and bathroom are order, so can be a tasks if you need to visit in the middle of the night. Spa is excellent.

formattedAddress: จ.สุราษฎร์ธานี 84310
location.state: จ.สุราษฎร์ธานี

venue.name: Le Méridien Koh Samui Resort & Spa

formattedAddress: จ.สุราษฎร์ธานี 84310
location.state: จ.สุราษฎร์ธานี

venue.name: Le Méridien Koh Samui Resort & Spa

tip.text: The breakfast buffet is average. The only good thing about this place is the view. Don't waste your $$$$ on food here.
One of the best things to do near Johannesburg. Do go for the mini safari, interact with the cheetah and play with lion cubs.
Amazing outdoor views, excellent wine collection along with delicious biltong.
One of the prettiest views of robin island and Cape Town. Be prepared to stand in a long line to go up and come back down. There is a hiking trail, be warned it can take you up to 2-4 hours to climb.

contact.facebookName: ท่าอากาศยานสุวรรณภูมิ | Suvarnabhumi Airport BKK

venue.name: Suvarnabhumi Airport (BKK) (ท่าอากาศยานสุวรรณภูมิ)

formattedAddress: สมุทรปราการ 10540
location.state: สมุทรปราการ

tip.text: One of the smallest and cutest airports. There is a Bangkok airways lounge with wifi on departure gate 1-2. When you land and depart, you board and deplane from the plane on the tarmac.

venue.name: Samui International Airport (USM) (ท่าอากาศยานนานาชาติสมุย)

location.state: จังหวัดสุราษฎร์ธานี

formattedAddress: สมุทรปราการ 10540
location.state: สมุทรปราการ

tip.text: The hotel is modern and with great facilities, but their service is extremely poor. Their staff provides a 2 star experience with a 5 star facility. I would not recommend the hotel to anyone.

venue.name: Four Seasons Hotel The Westcliff, Johannesburg

tip.text: Excellent views with outdoor seating available during summers. They have great music and cocktails. They have a lot of seating.
Beautiful hotel with spacious and luxurious rooms. Do go to their bar "vault" they have one of the best cocktails in Amsterdam. Try getting canal view rooms.
Try the shoyu ramen or pick from the vegan ramen which has the classic or tomato style. They even have pork and vegetarian gyoza

formattedAddress: 32 Varet St (btwn Graham Ave & Manhattan Ave)

tip.text: Vegetarian friendly place. Try the cold press juices and have the watermelon salad or the avocado toast. They also have lettuce tacos!
Definitely a trendy spot with beautiful decor. Get the wild mushroom pizza, bao buns and paella.
Summer is the best time to be here on the weekends. Sit and have a fun picnic with your friends or just relax and sunbath. Vendors will come and offer drinks and food. 15 acres of green pasture!

Get here early to avoid paying for tabs or table service. They have small bathrooms so usually there is a 20-30 minute waiting. Drinks are pricey but the music and view is great. Try their Moscow mule
Beautiful views and free entry. Weekend line starts forming around 10pm. Head here around 9pm and get yourself chairs facing the city next to the pool. Waitresses come around to take drink orders.

Pro tip: take meadowland bound train from secaucus, leave before your event ends to get back on train as it gets crowded. They have Chase ATM's. Cards accepted. Sit in lower levels for less voice echo

formattedAddress: 1 Metlife Stadium Dr (at Meadowlands Sports Complex)

tip.text: Order the momo's. Aloo dum is delicious. They also offer thali. This place is extremely reasonable and food is great. Vegetarian friendly.
Beautiful during peak bloom. Status can be tracked online. Come during weekdays to avoid the rush. Go near tidal basin.
For a quick and delicious burrito or taco head to this place. Order Burrito mojado. They even serve breakfast burritos. For vegetarians get the salsa maya, self serve salsa bar for added flavor!
Definitely try the mozzarella appetizer. Not worth the long wait! The momofuku ramen is overrated compared to other places in town such as ippudo!
A beautiful hotel with lots of history. An old monastery converted into a hotel. They still have 4 Catholic monks that stay here. They also sell an exclusive St.Augistine beer which you must try!

contact.facebookName: Augustine, a Luxury Collection Hotel, Prague

tip.text: Open 24 hours! Delicious Mexican fast food. Order a burrito for 125Kc and add gauc for 15Kc.
Best place for amazing collection of Belgian beer along with Provence style mussels. Do order some fresh oysters.
This is a beautiful coffee shop with a backyard. They offer macha! Get the Greek yogurt with rose petals!
Excellent for brunches! Get fresh grapefruit juice. Their wings are flavorful and crisp. They offer outdoor seating.
One of the hole in the wall Mexican place with amazing tortas. This place is cheap and offers authenticate flavor.
Great Mexican food with best happy hour. Order the fish tacos and their Guacamole. Don't forget to get yourself their cucumber or jalapeño margaritas.
Order the fresh orange juice along with market vegetables. They have an excellent veggie burger. Don't forget the avocado toast!
This place is Michelin star worthy! Beautiful presentation and delicious food. Go for chefs tasting, order the pathar beef kebab, duck chettinad, sweet pick rib, dal ghost and butter chicken naan.
Take your number, wait for them to call out. Try everything bagel with smoked salmon along with lox cream cheese. They also have excellent caviar creme cheese. Be prepared to wait. $10 min on CC

formattedAddress: 179 E Houston St (btwn Allen & Orchard St)

tip.text: Avoid the rush for lunch by getting in before 12pm. Also have their chicken bowl or Kafta bowl. Their orange and green sauce are a must drizzle on your bowl or sandwich. Fresh, tasty and reasonable...
3.4 KM long trail and 24USD per person. At max you would see a few sloths. Though the hanging bridges are an experience. Not sure if they are worth your time and money.
Beautiful views, don't hire a guide. 1 hour 30min trail with beautiful views of the volcano and the lakes. Also do see the 400 year old tree. Entry to the park is 15USD per person.
Beautiful property with amazing views. They have a hot spring and happy hours from 5-8pm. Also, their breakfast buffet is must have! The staff is really helpful. 15 min away from Arenal.

formattedAddress: 9 Km West and 3.5 km North of La Fortuna Centre (142)
location.address: 9 Km West and 3.5 km North of La Fortuna Centre

tip.text: Rio Celeste is a 15KM off-road and then about 20 min hike along with 200 steps. Do not go here during rainy season, it's very muddy!
Order the pork dumplings in chili oil along with scallion pancakes. The dry pepper style fish is delicious so is the garlic sauce style chicken. Don't forget to order Dan Dan noodles.
Beautiful views from tables by the window. Order the pancake sampler, beef tartare, kalbi (short ribs). For dessert, deconstructed snickers is on point. Order a glass of Fiery Julep.
Start your meal with Pigs feet( Grilled Pork Tonsoku), famous Gyoza. Must order Hakata Tonton hotpot. Go after 10pm for a small or no wait.
Best view of the Eiffel Tower! Would recommend sunset views to get best of both worlds. Beware of pickpockets.

formattedAddress: Place du Trocadéro et du 11 Novembre
location.address: Place du Trocadéro et du 11 Novembre

tip.text: Every first Sunday of the month entry is free! The audio tour is must take, make sure to visit the Mona Lisa and look for the upside down pyramid.
Climb 275 stairs to get the breathtaking view of champs elysees!

formattedAddress: Place Charles de Gaulle (Avenue des Champs-Élysées)

venue.name: Arc de Triomphe (Arc de Triomphe de l'Étoile)

tip.text: View all the stain glass work and then visit the top to see all of Paris! It's an architectural marvel from the past!

formattedAddress: 6 place du parvis Notre-Dame (Place Jean-Paul II)

venue.name: Cathedral of Notre Dame de Paris (Cathédrale Notre-Dame de Paris)

tip.text: €17 to go right to the top for adults! Make sure to view the Eiffel after sunset, it sparkles every first 5 min of every hour. The views are breathtaking.
You can never go wrong with the creme brûlée donut! Also try their vanilla and orange blossom donut! They also have seasonal specials!
Make sure you get a reservation to get a table right next to the views of the water. Must order their lamb gyro and calamari meatballs. Try coming during sunset and watch the breathtaking views!
Great property with scenic views. They have an excellent breakfast buffet with limited outdoor seating. Try their villa 515, which has an amazing garden and ocean view!

formattedAddress: Vivanta by Taj - Fort Aguada, Goa (Sinquerim, Candolim)
location.address: Vivanta by Taj - Fort Aguada, Goa

tip.text: Perfect for intimate dinners. Order the Avocado salad and their grilled halibut.

formattedAddress: 35 E 18th St (btwn Broadway & Park Ave S)

tip.text: Has scenic views of the Charles bridge! Get a corner table next to the river and enjoy some great selection of their own brews and food!
One of the most scenic views of Innsbruck. You can even trek up or take the lift up. Definitely going up and enjoy breathe of fresh air!
Very unique statues near the John Lennon wall and narrow lane. Definitely worth a visit!
A very trendy and uniquely decorated place with delicious confess and healthy eats. Order the chicken club sandwich. They also have great selections for the vegetarians.
Sit outdoor with free wifi, have a cocktail or coffee in their porch. With beautiful view of the lake and mountains.
One of the prettiest small towns in Europe, come on a sunny day and rent a boat for €13 to go into the water for 30 min. Sit outdoor and grab a nice hot coffee! Enjoy the beautiful view!
Do book the audio tour and save yourself 1.5 hours to go through the tour thoroughly. It is one of the most beautiful architecture marvel you will witness!

venue.name: Sagrada Família (Templo Expiatorio de la Sagrada Familia)

tip.text: They have one of the best tapas in Barcelona! You have to try the house wine and their ham. The grilled calamari with pesto is spot on delicious. This place is very inexpensive. Eat at the bar!
You cannot go wrong with burgers here. Though pricey for burgers overall. They do have the option of wagyu beef! And you can always select multiple toppings for a small price. Do get the fries!
One of the most beautiful views of London with an incredible meal. Do order the shrimp tempura in appetizers and also order samba London roles. Do come with a reservation and wait at their tree bar!
Must attend Axwell and Ingrosso here during the summer. They have amazing performances and the visuals they create are mind blowing. If you haven't partied here, you haven't partied at all!

formattedAddress: 07817 San Jose de la Atalaya Islas Baleares

tip.text: Best food in Delhi hands down! Order Dal Ghost, butter chicken naan and mushroom truffle naan. They have excellent service with attention to details. Also try the cocktail marigold
The higher floors have a great view. Do not miss the breakfast at Oscar, it has delicious and a great variety of food to please your pallet. Shoe shine and wifi in lobby are complimentary.
Scallion pancake with beef are the best dish on the menu. There crab and spicy dumplings are just order. They always have a wait!
Usually known for ballet shows! They also known to bring renowned orchestra shows often such as LOTR by Howard Shore. Get the orchestra middle seating for the best unobstructed views!

formattedAddress: Lincoln Center Plaza (at W 63rd St & Columbus Ave)

tip.text: One of the recommended tours in Amsterdam! They walk you through the full process of brewing and end the tour on a high note with a glass of chilled Heineken!
Must have the fried chicken for brunch! Do try the kimchi fried rice with the sunny side up! This place always has a wait, please make sure you have a reservation.
Must try lemon basil and rosewater! You can never go wrong with vanilla bean.
Do order the French onion soup burger for brunch! And the quinoa salad is a must try.
As a beginner this is idle for skiing. They have the buddy slopes and then gradual level increases. Make sure you have your ski pants before hand, shops here are relatively more expensive.
Great place for dates, a tiny spot in west village with excellent Italian food paired with a large selection of wines. Do order the bruschetta and mussels.

formattedAddress: 21 Bedford St (btwn Downing St and 6th Ave)

tip.text: They have one of the best steaks in NYC! My personal favorite is their Cajun rib eye steak! A fair share of warning, if you are a small eater, share the steak as it is HUGE! Crab cakes is a must!!
The hakata delux miso based is a must order.
The Belgian style mussels are really good. Reasonable prices for seafood.
This is hands down one of the most beautiful hotels in Amsterdam. The room sizes are bigger than many other hotels near by. It is the epitome of luxury.
Beautiful temple with a great history! It is currently under renovation though open to public.
You have to watch a match if you are a tennis fan! Excellent venue and an amazing experience. It is a treat to watch the best players battle it out!

formattedAddress: USTA Billie Jean King National Tennis Center
location.address: USTA Billie Jean King National Tennis Center

tip.text: Pacman dumplings and famous Katz Deli's pastrami pastry is really delicious!
The view is one of the best from this rooftop! Now they have a DJ on the rooftop also. Get here early, can be difficult to get a place to sit.
Chicken with kidney beans is very unique and tastes exotic
Imperial chicken and pecking duck are two dishes you do not want to miss
It's always crowded! To get the perfect picture you must take a panorama
This is one of the best Japanese restaurants in Amsterdam. Great selection of fish. Try the halibut.
A pretty cool looking coffee shop! Pretty reasonable and a great selection
Get a canal facing room.
